  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Carnival registration allows clubs to express interest in participating in Masters Rugby League carnivals. The process involves registering your club, managing your team roster, and coordinating with carnival organizers.</p>

  <h3>Types of Carnival Registration</h3>

  <h4>Club Registration</h4>
  <p>Express interest in attending a carnival as a participating club:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Interest Registration</strong> — Submit initial interest with expected player count</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Information</strong> — Provide team contact details and special requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Review Process</strong> — Carnival organizers review and approve registrations</li>
    <li><strong>Team Formation</strong> — Build your team roster after approval</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Carnival Creation</h4>
  <p>Create and manage your own carnival events:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Event Setup</strong> — Define carnival details, dates, and registration settings</li>
    <li><strong>Club Management</strong> — Review and approve club registrations</li>
    <li><strong>Team Coordination</strong> — Manage participating teams and player assignments</li>
    <li><strong>Event Administration</strong> — Handle all aspects of carnival organization</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Registering Your Club for a Carnival</h3>

  <h4>Finding Carnivals</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Browse Events</strong> — Visit the carnivals page to see upcoming events</li>
    <li><strong>Review Details</strong> — Check carnival information, dates, location, and hosting club</li>
    <li><strong>Check Eligibility</strong> — Ensure your club meets any participation requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Express Interest</strong> — Use the registration section if available</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Registration Process</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Registration</strong> — Navigate to the carnival page and locate the "Register Interest" section</li>
    <li><strong>Provide Player Count</strong> — Estimate the number of players who might attend</li>
    <li><strong>Team Information</strong> — Enter your team name (optional) and contact details</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Details</strong> — Provide primary contact person, email, and phone</li>
    <li><strong>Special Requirements</strong> — Note any special needs, accommodations, or requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Submit Registration</strong> — Click "Register Interest" to submit your application</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Registration Information Required</h4>

  <h5>Basic Information</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Expected Player Count</strong> — Approximate number of players (helps organizers plan)</li>
    <li><strong>Team Name</strong> — Optional custom team name (defaults to club name)</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Person</strong> — Primary contact for carnival communications</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Email</strong> — Email address for carnival updates and coordination</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Phone</strong> — Phone number for urgent communications</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Special Requirements</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Accommodation Needs</strong> — If your team needs accommodation arrangements</li>
    <li><strong>Dietary Requirements</strong> — Any team-wide dietary considerations</li>
    <li><strong>Equipment Needs</strong> — Special equipment or facilities requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Considerations</strong> — Team medical needs or emergency contacts</li>
    <li><strong>Travel Logistics</strong> — Transportation or parking requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Other Notes</strong> — Any additional information for organizers</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Managing Your Team After Registration</h3>

  <h4>Team Roster Management</h4>
  <p>Once your registration is approved, you can manage your team's player roster:</p>

  <h5>Adding Players to Your Team</h5>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Team Management</strong> — Go to your registered carnival and find the team management section</li>
    <li><strong>Select Players</strong> — Choose from your club's available players</li>
    <li><strong>Multiple Selection</strong> — You can select multiple players at once for efficient team building</li>
    <li><strong>Review Selections</strong> — Check that all selected players are correct</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Addition</strong> — Add the selected players to your carnival team</li>
  </ol>

  <h5>Player Availability</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Available Players</strong> — Players from your club who haven't been assigned to this carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Already Assigned</strong> — Players already on your team roster</li>
    <li><strong>Player Status</strong> — Active players are available for selection</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Information</strong> — Access player medical notes and emergency contacts</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Team Communication</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Team Announcements</strong> — Communicate with your carnival team</li>
    <li><strong>Event Updates</strong> — Receive updates from carnival organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Schedule Changes</strong> — Stay informed about any changes to carnival schedule</li>
    <li><strong>Logistics Coordination</strong> — Coordinate travel, accommodation, and meeting arrangements</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Carnival Organizer Responsibilities</h3>

  <h4>Managing Registrations</h4>
  <p>If you're organizing a carnival, you have additional responsibilities:</p>

  <h5>Registration Review</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Review Applications</strong> — Evaluate club registration requests</li>
    <li><strong>Contact Clubs</strong> — Communicate with registering clubs about their applications</li>
    <li><strong>Approval Process</strong> — Approve or decline registration requests</li>
    <li><strong>Team Limits</strong> — Manage team size limits and participation rules</li>
  </ul>

  <h5>Team Management</h5>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Monitor Teams</strong> — Track registered teams and player assignments</li>
    <li><strong>Player Coordination</strong> — Help clubs coordinate their player selections</li>
    <li><strong>Communication Hub</strong> — Facilitate communication between teams and organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Event Logistics</strong> — Manage overall event coordination and planning</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Registration Best Practices</h3>

  <h4>Planning and Preparation</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Early Registration</strong> — Register as early as possible to secure your spot</li>
    <li><strong>Accurate Information</strong> — Provide complete and accurate contact information</li>
    <li><strong>Player Availability</strong> — Ensure your players are available for the carnival dates</li>
    <li><strong>Team Requirements</strong> — Understand and meet any team size or composition requirements</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Communication</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stay Informed</strong> — Regularly check for updates from carnival organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Respond Promptly</strong> — Reply to organizer communications in a timely manner</li>
    <li><strong>Team Coordination</strong> — Keep your team informed about carnival details and requirements</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Contacts</strong> — Ensure all emergency contact information is up to date</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Logistics Planning</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Travel Arrangements</strong> — Plan transportation to and from the carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Accommodation</strong> — Arrange accommodation if required</li>
    <li><strong>Equipment Preparation</strong> — Ensure all necessary equipment is ready</li>
    <li><strong>Medical Preparation</strong> — Review player medical information and emergency procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Registration Status Tracking</h3>

  <h4>Status Types</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pending</strong> — Registration submitted, awaiting organizer review</li>
    <li><strong>Approved</strong> — Registration approved, can now manage team</li>
    <li><strong>Declined</strong> — Registration not approved by organizers</li>
    <li><strong>Withdrawn</strong> — Club withdrew their registration</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Status Monitoring</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Dashboard Updates</strong> — Check your dashboard for registration status updates</li>
    <li><strong>Email Notifications</strong> — Receive email updates about your registration status</li>
    <li><strong>Carnival Page</strong> — Visit the carnival page to see current registration status</li>
    <li><strong>Organizer Communication</strong> — Contact organizers if you have questions about your status</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Withdrawal and Cancellation</h3>

  <h4>Withdrawing Registration</h4>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Access Registration</strong> — Go to your registered carnival</li>
    <li><strong>Find Withdrawal Option</strong> — Look for the unregister or withdraw option</li>
    <li><strong>Confirm Withdrawal</strong> — Confirm that you want to withdraw your registration</li>
    <li><strong>Notify Team</strong> — Inform your team members about the withdrawal</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>Cancellation Policies</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Refund Policies</strong> — Check carnival-specific refund and cancellation policies</li>
    <li><strong>Timeline Considerations</strong> — Be aware of cancellation deadlines</li>
    <li><strong>Team Impact</strong> — Consider the impact on your team and other participants</li>
    <li><strong>Organizer Communication</strong> — Communicate directly with organizers about cancellations</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Troubleshooting Registration Issues</h3>

  <h4>Common Issues</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Registration Not Visible</strong> — Ensure you're logged in as a club delegate</li>
    <li><strong>Cannot Register</strong> — Check if the carnival is still accepting registrations</li>
    <li><strong>Form Errors</strong> — Ensure all required fields are completed correctly</li>
    <li><strong>No Players Available</strong> — Make sure you have active players in your club roster</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Getting Help</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contact Organizers</strong> — Reach out to the carnival organizing club</li>
    <li><strong>Check Documentation</strong> — Review carnival-specific registration instructions</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Support</strong> — Contact platform support for technical issues</li>
    <li><strong>Community Forums</strong> — Check community discussions for common solutions</li>
  </ul>

